    steps:[{text:'Heat milk in a heavy-bottomed pot over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until it reaches 180°F. This denatures the proteins for a thicker, creamier yogurt.',timer:null}, {text:'Remove from heat and cool to 110°F — about 30–45 minutes at room temperature, or faster in a cold water bath. Use a thermometer. Too hot kills the culture; too cool slows fermentation.',timer:37}, {text:'Whisk starter yogurt into a small amount of the warm milk, then stir back into the full pot until completely combined.',timer:null}, {text:'Pour into clean glass jars and place in your incubation spot — oven with light on (typically 100–110°F), a yogurt maker, or a cooler with a hot water bottle.',timer:null}, {text:'Incubate undisturbed for 8–12 hours. The longer it incubates, the tangier and thicker it becomes.',timer:null}, {text:'Refrigerate at least 2 hours before eating — yogurt thickens significantly as it cools.',timer:null}, {text:'Reserve 2 tbsp as your starter for the next batch.',timer:null}],
